\begin{abstract}
This note was produced automatically from CSV extracts in the CMS Jupyter education bundle.
It summarizes invariant-mass distributions and basic statistics for dimuon samples from Run~2011A open data.
These results illustrate resonance peaks and background shapes used in introductory analyses.
They do \emph{not} reproduce the combined Higgs discovery analysis (e.g.\ CMS arXiv:1207.7235).
\end{abstract}

\section{Method}
For \texttt{Zmumu\_Run2011A.csv}, dimuon invariant mass is computed as in the CMS notebook \texttt{Calculate-invariant-mass.ipynb}:
\begin{equation}
M = \sqrt{2 p_{T,1} p_{T,2}\left(\cosh(\eta_1-\eta_2)-\cos(\phi_1-\phi_2)\right)}\,.
\end{equation}
Other CSV files already contain a column \texttt{M}.

